: Defines a time period in which a customer may give notice or request a change to their contract capacity (i.e., increase or decrease), terminate service on the large load tariff, and/or take service on a different tariff. Change/Exit Fees: Defines fees a customer may need to pay to the utility to reduce their contract capacity during a particular time period, terminate service on the large load tariff, and/or take service on a different one. Security Reductions/Release: Defines or allows options for the utility to revise the customer\\u2019s current deposit or collateral requirements, such as to reflect customer operational changes, changes to the financial condition of the customer or guarantor, market conditions, etc.; 'energy_transition_provisions'-Tariff includes options for customers to pursue energy transition objectives, or explicitly references the availability of separate riders for this purpose. These may include time-of-use (TOU) pricing, interruptible service agreements, clean or renewable energy riders, Clean Transition Tariffs, and other related mechanisms. Several examples are noted in this database.\"\n}",
