      "text": "Skip to content\n\nEnergy Market Insights Powered by Earth Etch\n\nSubscribe\n\nSign In\n\nOpen menu\n\n×\n\nSubscribe\n\nEnergize\n\n# Market Alerts\n\n## TX – CNP Transmission Cost Recovery Factor (TCRF) Approved Effective September 1, 2025 – Final\n\nPublished August 29, 2025\n\nCategory: Texas\n\nRelated Categories: CenterPoint Energy, Electric, Market Alert, REP, TCRF True-up Market\n\nNotice Date: August 28, 2025\nNotice Type: Final\n\nShort Description: On Tuesday, July 08, 2025, the Public Utility Commission of Texas (PUCT) issued a Notice of Approval for the TCRF True-up filing under Docket No. 58178 with no changes from the original filing.\n\nIntended Audience: Competitive Retailers\n\nLong Description: This is a reminder that on Tuesday, July 08, 2025, the Public Utility Commission of Texas (PUCT) issued a Notice of Approval for the TCRF True-up filing under Docket No. 58178 with no changes from the original filing. This filing has an effective date of September 1, 2025.\n\nAdditional Information: This is the final market notice regarding this TCRF update.\n\nCompetitive Retailer Relations\nCenterPoint Energy Houston Electric, LLC\n\n---\n\nCopyright 2026 MAGNIFYI.com. Unauthorized copying, retransmission, or republication prohibited. You are not permitted to copy any work or text of MAGNIFYI.com without the separate and express written consent of MAGNIFYI.com.\n\n← Previous Market Alert Next Market Alert →\n\nEditor’s Picks\n\n Pennsylvania PUC Adopts Proposed Model Tariff for Large Load Customers \n\n Podcasts EMC’s The Energy Insider Podcast Episode 19 Now Available on MAGNIFYI.com \n\n Maryland Wide Ranging Comments Filed in Response to Consultant’s Resource Adequacy White Paper \n\n New York Wide Range of Comments Filed as to Whether Investor-owned Utilities Should Own Generation Facilities, Including Renewable Generation Facilities \n\n FCC Improving Customer Service and Protecting Consumers Through Onshoring \n\nTrending\n\n Texas Battle of the Balance Sheets: The New Reality of Competition in Texas Retail Energy \n\n Pennsylvania PUC Adopts Proposed Model Tariff for Large Load Customers \n\n Flexible Capacity Flexible Capacity Could Flourish With Policy Changes, Paper Says \n\n Ohio Supreme Court Declines to Hear Appeal of Former Ohio House Speaker’s HB1 Bribery Scheme \n\n Energy Marketing Conferences Top Ten Lessons Learned at EMC25 \n\n## News Categories\n\nBroker / Supplier\n\nCompliance\n\nCustomer Protection\n\nEDI / Billing / Collection\n\nElectric\n\nEnergy Storage\n\nGas\n\nISO/RTO\n\nLarge Loads\n\nLegislation\n\nLicense Applications\n\nNet Metering\n\nPurchase of Receivable (POR)\n\nRenewable Energy\n\nResource Adequacy\n\nRulemaking\n\nUtility\n\nViolation\n\nSubscribe\n\nSign In\n\nSubscribe\n\nSign In\n\nAbout MAGNIFYI® | Advertise with MAGNIFYI® | MAGNIFYI® FAQs | Contact MAGNIFYI®\n\nCopyright © 2026 MAGNIFYI**®**, All Rights Reserved Privacy Policy | Terms of Use\n\n##### Change Location\n\n###### Find awesome listings near you!\n\nChange Location\n\n```json\n{\"@context\":\"https://schema.org\",\"@graph\":[{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"@id\":\"https://magnifyi.com/#organization\",\"name\":\"MAGNIFYI\",\"url\":\"https://magnifyi.com\"},{\"@type\":\"WebSite\",\"@id\":\"https://magnifyi.com/#website\",\"url\":\"https://magnifyi.com\",\"name\":\"MAGNIFYI\",\"publisher\":{\"@id\":\"https://magnifyi.com/#organization\"},\"inLanguage\":\"en-US\"},{\"@type\":\"ImageObject\",\"@id\":\"https://magnifyi.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/MAGNIFYI-Social-Share-Image.jpg\",\"url\":\"https://magnifyi.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/MAGNIFYI-Social-Share-Image.jpg\",\"width\":\"1200\",\"height\":\"628\",\"inLanguage\":\"en-US\"},{\"@type\":\"WebPage\",\"@id\":\"https://magnifyi.com/tx-cnp-transmission-cost-recovery-factor-tcrf-approved-effective-september-1-2025-final/#webpage\",\"url\":\"https://magnifyi.com/tx-cnp-transmission-cost-recovery-factor-tcrf-approved-effective-september-1-2025-fina